article.headline: Ohio 77, Akron 72
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio (AP) -- Leon Williams scored 19 points and Sonny Troutman added 14, including a 3-pointer that put Ohio ahead for good with about five minutes left, as the Bobcats defeated Akron 77-72 on Saturday night. Williams was 8-of-11 shooting for Ohio (10-4, 1-0 Mid-American Conference) and had eight rebounds. Bubba Walther added 16 points and Jerome Tillman had 12 points and five rebounds. Akron (9-4, 0-1) led 37-36 at halftime. The lead changed six times in the second half before Ohio pulled ahead with 5:18 remaining on Troutman's 3-pointer, which started a 11-0 run that gave the Bobcats a 72-62 lead. The Zips twice cut the deficit to two points on jumpers by Romeo Travis in the final two minutes but couldn't take the lead. Travis had 13 points and nine rebounds, Nick Dials added 10 points and Cedrick Middleton led the Zips with 20 points. Both teams grabbed 36 rebounds. Ohio shot 48 percent (24-of-50) to Akron's 47 percent (27-of-57), but the Bobcats made 22-of-35 foul shots, compared to Akron's 11-of-14.
